aa(lp261
VSo to test this we used a machine that we have
p262
aVcalled the Blicket Detector.
p263
aVThis is a box that lights up and plays music
p264
aVwhen you put some things on it and not others.
p265
aVAnd using this very simple machine,
p266
aVmy lab and others have done dozens of studies
p267
aVshowing just how good babies are
p268
aVat learning about the world.
p269
aVLet me mention just one
p270
aVthat we did with Tumar Kushner, my student.
p271
aVIf I showed you this detector,
p272
aVyou would be likely to think to begin with
p273
aVthat the way to make the detector go
p274
aVwould be to put a block on top of the detector.
p275
aVBut actually, this detector
p276
aVworks in a bit of a strange way.
p277
aVBecause if you wave a block over the top of the detector,
p278
aVsomething you wouldn't ever think of to begin with,
p279
aVthe detector will actually activate two out of three times.
p280
aVWhereas, if you do the likely thing, put the block on the detector,
p281
aVit will only activate two out of six times.
p282
aVSo the unlikely hypothesis
p283
aVactually has stronger evidence.
p284
aVIt looks as if the waving
p285
aVis a more effective strategy than the other strategy.
p286
aVSo we did just this; we gave four year-olds this pattern of evidence,
p287
aVand we just asked them to make it go.
p288
aVAnd sure enough, the four year-olds used the evidence
p289
aVto wave the object on top of the detector.
p290
aa(lp291
VNow there are two things that are really interesting about this.
p292
aVThe first one is, again, remember, these are four year-olds.
p293
aVThey're just learning how to count.
p294
aVBut unconsciously,
p295
aVthey're doing these quite complicated calculations
p296
aVthat will give them a conditional probability measure.
p297
aVAnd the other interesting thing
p298
aVis that they're using that evidence
p299
aVto get to an idea, get to a hypothesis about the world,
p300
aVthat seems very unlikely to begin with.
p301
aVAnd in studies we've just been doing in my lab, similar studies,
p302
aVwe've show that four year-olds are actually better
p303
aVat finding out an unlikely hypothesis
p304
aVthan adults are when we give them exactly the same task.
p305
aVSo in these circumstances,
p306
aVthe children are using statistics to find out about the world,
p307
aVbut after all, scientists also do experiments,
p308
aVand we wanted to see if children are doing experiments.
